# Force LF line endings on source + shipped files.
#
# Windows-specific rationale: Git's `core.autocrlf=true` default on
# Windows rewrites LF to CRLF on checkout. When Claude Code invokes
# a hook via Git Bash, bash reads the script's shebang — CRLF makes
# it search for an interpreter named `node\r`, which doesn't exist,
# and the hook silently never runs. Even though our hook command
# bypasses the shebang (we invoke `node.exe pretool.js` explicitly),
# bundled docs, settings JSON, and JSON-parsed at runtime would all
# break similarly under CRLF contamination. Pin everything to LF.
*.js   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
